fe trading environment.\n\nHowever, there are legitimate ways to indirectly donate Robux or support others within the Roblox community:\n\n<h3>Using Group Payouts to Share Robux<\/h3>\n\nOne of the most popular methods for donating Robux involves Roblox Groups. If you create or belong to a group, you can pool Robux into the group’s funds and distribute payouts to group members. Here’s how this works:\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Create or join a Roblox Group:<\/strong> Groups serve as communities and can hold Robux in their balance.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Earn or deposit Robux into the group:<\/strong> Group funds can grow through sales of group items, game passes, or by depositing your own Robux.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Distribute payouts:<\/strong> Group admins can send Robux payouts to members as donations or rewards.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\nThis method is commonly used by content creators who want to reward contributors or friends. Keep in mind, though, that only group owners and those with payout permissions can send Robux to members.\n\n<h3>Buying and Gifting Game Passes or Items<\/h3>\n\nAnother creative way to donate Robux is by purchasing game passes, avatar items, or limited items and gifting them to friends. While there isn’t a direct gifting feature for Robux or most items, some developers offer gifting options for game passes or in-game items.\n\nYou can also purchase limited items from the Avatar Shop and then sell them to friends at a discounted rate or trade items. This approach requires coordination and trust, as it involves trading rather than a simple donation.\n\n<h2>Supporting Creators Through Game Passes and Developer Products<\/h2>\n\nIf your goal is to support a game developer or creator on Roblox, buying their game passes or developer products is effectively a way to “donate” Robux to them. When you purchase these items, a portion of your Robux goes directly to the creator’s account.\n\nThis method is encouraged by Roblox as it helps creators earn revenue and